From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Imanol-Mikel Barba <imanol@local>
Date: Sun, 1 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] mmc: add MMC_CAP2_WIFI_RK915 flag and DT property

The Rockchip RK915 WiFi/BT SDIO chip requires several quirks in the
MMC subsystem:
  - CMD52 must wait for previous data completion (PRV_DAT_WAIT)
  - Low power clock gating must be disabled
  - CIS tuple parsing must be relaxed

Add a new caps2 flag MMC_CAP2_WIFI_RK915 (bit 29) and parse the
"supports-rk915" boolean DT property to set it. This flag is then
checked by dw_mmc and sdio_cis patches.

Signed-off-by: Imanol-Mikel Barba <imanol@local>
---
 drivers/mmc/core/host.c  | 2 ++
 include/linux/mmc/host.h | 1 +
 2 files changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/include/linux/mmc/host.h b/include/linux/mmc/host.h
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/include/linux/mmc/host.h
+++ b/include/linux/mmc/host.h
@@ -465,6 +465,7 @@ struct mmc_host {
 #define MMC_CAP2_CRYPTO		0
 #endif
 #define MMC_CAP2_ALT_GPT_TEGRA	(1 << 28)	/* Host with eMMC that has GPT entry at a non-standard location */
+#define MMC_CAP2_WIFI_RK915	(1 << 29)	/* Rockchip RK915 WiFi SDIO quirks */
 
 	int			fixed_drv_type;	/* fixed driver type for non-removable media */
 
diff --git a/drivers/mmc/core/host.c b/drivers/mmc/core/host.c
index 333333333333..444444444444 100644
--- a/drivers/mmc/core/host.c
+++ b/drivers/mmc/core/host.c
@@ -405,6 +405,8 @@ int mmc_of_parse(struct mmc_host *host)
 		host->caps2 |= MMC_CAP2_NO_SD;
 	if (device_property_read_bool(dev, "no-mmc"))
 		host->caps2 |= MMC_CAP2_NO_MMC;
+	if (device_property_read_bool(dev, "supports-rk915"))
+		host->caps2 |= MMC_CAP2_WIFI_RK915;
 	if (device_property_read_bool(dev, "no-mmc-hs400"))
 		host->caps2 &= ~(MMC_CAP2_HS400_1_8V | MMC_CAP2_HS400_1_2V |
 				 MMC_CAP2_HS400_ES);
